    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>MEDIATION FOR CANADIAN PILOTS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Timothy Pritchard</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Pritchard, Timothy</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Air Canada and union representing its 2,200 pilots agree to nonbinding mediation that could lead to new contract; also agree there will be no strike or lockout as long as talks continue (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>At the urging of the federal Labor Minister, Claudette Bradshaw, Air Canada and the union representing its 2,200 pilots have agreed to nonbinding mediation that could lead to a new contract. They have also agreed there will be no strike or lockout as long as the talks continue. They are expected to last at least two weeks. Air Canada handles more than 80 percent of Canada's domestic air traffic. The pilots have been without a contract since April 1.</p>
        <p>Timothy Pritchard</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
